## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

### Summary

| Severity | Count |
|----------|-------|
| **Critical** | 6 |
| **High** | 0 |
| **Medium** | 2 |
| **Low** | 1 |

This is a textbook **coverage-touching** test class. Every public method on `ProductCatalog` is called (giving you 95%+ line coverage), but almost nothing is actually *verified*. These tests will pass even if every method returns garbage or silently corrupts data.

---

### Critical Findings

#### 1. Coverage Touching (Systemic)

The class methodically calls every method on `ProductCatalog` without meaningful assertions. 6 of 10 tests have **zero assertions**; the remaining 4 use only `Assert.IsNotNull` — a trivially passing check since the production code always returns non-null collections/strings.

---

#### 2. No Assertions — `AddProduct_Works` (line 17)

```csharp
// BEFORE — proves nothing
_catalog.AddProduct(product);

// AFTER — verify the product is retrievable
_catalog.AddProduct(product);
var stored = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.AreEqual("Widget", stored?.Name);
Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, stored?.Price);
```

#### 3. No Assertions — `UpdatePrice_Works` (line 31)

```csharp
// BEFORE
_catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);

// AFTER — verify price actually changed
_catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);
var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated!.Price);
```

#### 4. No Assertions — `RemoveProduct_Works` (line 39)

```csharp
// BEFORE
_catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");

// AFTER — verify product is gone
_catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.IsNull(_catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001"));
```

#### 5. No Assertions — `GetProductCount_Works` (line 63)

```csharp
// BEFORE
var count = _catalog.GetProductCount();

// AFTER
_catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
var count = _catalog.GetProductCount();
Assert.AreEqual(1, count);
```

#### 6. No Assertions — `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (line 69)

This is the most dangerous gap — a 10% discount could calculate wrong and you'd never know.

```csharp
// BEFORE
_catalog.ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m);

// AFTER — verify prices were reduced correctly
_catalog.ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m);
var widget = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.AreEqual(8.991m, widget!.Price);   // 9.99 * 0.90
